OL,3,CPlans unveiled for low traffic
OL,4,Cneighbourhood in South Bristol
OL,6,FBristol City Council claims the
OL,7,Fchanges would "create a better
OL,8,Fbalance" between how streets are used,
OL,9,Fmaking them safer, quieter and less
OL,10,Fpolluted. The project is the second
OL,11,Fone in the city, with a similar scheme
OL,12,Fplanned for Barton Hill, Redfield and
OL,13,FSt George.
OL,15,FA new public consultation is giving
OL,16,Fpeople the chance to have their say
OL,17,Fabout what changes should be made to
OL,18,Fthe roads across an area stretching
OL,19,Ffrom Ashton Vale to Totterdown.
